main event: On March 25, 1966, an observer reported seeing two lights traveling in different directions over Macon, Georgia.
interesting points: The observation lasted for a total of 10 minutes for one object and 4 minutes for the other., The first object was seen in the southeast and disappeared in the southwest., The second object was traveling northeast and crossed paths with the first., The investigator suggested the objects could have been commercial aircraft., The observer was described as a sound-minded individual with a high educational level.
witness description: A 42-year-old male, owner and operator of an equipment company.
